# Frontend-Specific Environment Variables
#
# IMPORTANT: This file is loaded by Vite AFTER .env.local
# Most configuration is inherited from ../env via .env.local (auto-generated)
#
# Setup:
#   1. Ensure ../env exists with VITE_* variables
#   2. Run ./sync-env.sh to generate .env.local from root .env
#   3. (Optional) cp fe/.env.example fe/.env to add frontend-specific overrides
#   4. Run: npm run dev
#
# The loading order is:
#   1. .env (this file's template)
#   2. .env.local (auto-generated from ../env)
#   3. .env (your overrides, if it exists)
#
# Variables inherited from ../env (via .env.local):
#   - VITE_API_URL
#   - VITE_MOCK_DATA
#   - VITE_AVAILABLE_LOCALES
#   - VITE_POSTS_PER_PAGE
#   - VITE_POST_PREVIEW_LIMIT

# Optional Overrides
# Uncomment and modify these only if you need different values than ../env:

# Backend API URL
# For local development with backend on different port:
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Mock Data Mode
# VITE_MOCK_DATA=true

# Available Locales
# VITE_AVAILABLE_LOCALES=en,it

# Pagination
# VITE_POSTS_PER_PAGE=5

# Post Preview Limit
# VITE_POST_PREVIEW_LIMIT=100
